Document: CameraAttributesPhysical
Path: godot/classes/class_cameraattributesphysical.rst
Summary: Defines physical camera attributes for rendering.

Inherits: CameraAttributes < Resource

This class allows you to define physical camera attributes for rendering. These attributes are used to simulate real-world camera properties, affecting how light interacts with the scene and how the final image is rendered. This is particularly useful for achieving photorealistic results in your Godot projects.
