Document: CameraAttributesPhysical
Path: godot/classes/class_cameraattributesphysical.rst
Summary: Describes the CameraAttributesPhysical class, its purpose in controlling rendering settings like exposure and depth of field, and how it interacts with other nodes like WorldEnvironment and Camera3D.

CameraAttributesPhysical is used to set rendering settings based on a physically-based camera's settings. It is responsible for exposure, auto-exposure, and depth of field.

When used in a WorldEnvironment it provides default settings for exposure, auto-exposure, and depth of field that will be used by all cameras without their own CameraAttributes, including the editor camera. When used in a Camera3D it will override any CameraAttributes set in the WorldEnvironment and will override the Camera3D's Camera3D.far, Camera3D.near, Camera3D.fov, and Camera3D.keep_aspect properties. When used in VoxelGI or LightmapGI, only the exposure settings will be used.

The default settings are intended for use in an outdoor environment, tips for settings for use in an indoor environment can be found in each setting's documentation.

Note: Depth of field blur is only supported in the Forward+ and Mobile rendering methods, not Compatibility.

Note: Auto-exposure is only supported in the Forward+ rendering method, not Mobile or Compatibility.
---CHUNK---
Document: CameraAttributesPhysical
Path: godot/classes/class_cameraattributesphysical.rst
Summary: This document describes the CameraAttributesPhysical class, which provides physical properties for cameras in Godot.

Inherits: CameraAttributes < Resource

Properties
name (float): The focal length of the camera in millimeters. Default: 50.0.
exposure (float): The exposure value (EV) of the camera. Higher values mean brighter images. Default: 1.0.
shutter_speed (float): The shutter speed of the camera in seconds. Default: 0.0166667.
aperture (float): The aperture (f-number) of the camera. Lower values mean shallower depth of field. Default: 1.8.
---CHUNK---
Document: CameraAttributesPhysical
Path: godot/classes/class_cameraattributesphysical.rst
Summary: Defines the properties for physical camera attributes, including exposure and frustum settings.

Properties
* auto_exposure_max_exposure_value (float): The maximum exposure value for auto-exposure. Default: 10.0
* auto_exposure_min_exposure_value (float): The minimum exposure value for auto-exposure. Default: -8.0
* exposure_aperture (float): The aperture value (f-stop) for exposure. Default: 16.0
* exposure_shutter_speed (float): The shutter speed value for exposure. Default: 100.0
* frustum_far (float): The far clipping plane distance for the frustum. Default: 4000.0
* frustum_focal_length (float): The focal length of the camera lens. Default: 35.0
* frustum_focus_distance (float): The distance at which the camera is focused. Default: 10.0
* frustum_near (float): The near clipping plane distance for the frustum. Default: 0.05
